result.name: Cafe 100%

reviews.text: The one at Wonderland Villas is probably the best of the chain restaurants.

Quite a pleasant cafe. Decent hygiene as this place only opened in early 2018. They have their own bakery, so definitely try their buns which are especially tasty when hot. The menu is simple and good value. Service is fine and fast when it's not busy. The only gripe I have is that it seems that the bakery staff do not operate the tills, although it is inside their station. Staff are not attentive enough to realise there are customers waiting to pay their bill. My regular breakfast hotspot, would recommend.
Nice place to dine in. Fair price. Food is okay.
no choice but this cafe, nightmare of wonderland residents
The only food outlet in this district.  They should do better with food quality & service, which can be a problem.

reviews.text: One restaurant, one coffee shop, a supermarket, and a laundry shop - not much else. Set up mainly for local residents.
An adequate commercial complex serving a relatively remote housing estate.
My place. In hong kong

Other than a Wellcome supermarket, Pacific Coffee and a Cafe 100%, there are plenty of empty stores. Unscrupulous landlords driving out shops with their ridiculous rent increases. They would rather have empty stores than to lower rent to attract more tenants and give customers a better variety of shops. Pretty disgusting behaviour for consumers. Shame on you.

reviews.text: 有自已麵包店👍
食物種類選擇多，座位舒適，停車場有1小時免費泊車
食物出品，以呢個價位，都可算在水準之上，尤其是華景山莊分店哪一間，又可以有一小時的免費停車，頗受到職業司機的愛戴
第一次幫襯百份百，食物質素很高，今次點了咖哩鷄扒飯，和犀飛利脆麵。當見到這碟脆麵時，真的笑了出來，因為很像一個爆炸頭，很搞笑，當然麵的確很脆。整體來說，有心經營，價錢合理，值得一試。
